21#ifndef _ELF_SPU_H
22#define _ELF_SPU_H
23
24#include "elf/reloc-macros.h"

26/* elf32-spu.c depends on these being consecutive. */
27START_RELOC_NUMBERS (elf_spu_reloc_type)
28 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_NONE, 0)
29 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR10, 1)
30 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR16, 2)
31 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR16_HI, 3)
32 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR16_LO, 4)
33 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR18, 5)
34 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR32, 6)
35 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_REL16, 7)
36 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR7, 8)
37 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_REL9, 9)
38 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_REL9I, 10)
39 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR10I, 11)
40 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR16I, 12)
41 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_REL32, 13)
42 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADDR16X, 14)
43 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_PPU32, 15)
44 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_PPU64, 16)
45 RELOC_NUMBER (R_SPU_ADD_PIC, 17)
46END_RELOC_NUMBERS (R_SPU_max)
47
48/* Program header extensions */
49
50/* Mark a PT_LOAD segment as containing an overlay which should not
51 initially be loaded. */
52#define PF_OVERLAY (1 << 27)
53
54/* SPU Dynamic Object Information. */
55#define PT_SPU_INFO 0x70000000
56
57/* SPU plugin information */
58#define SPU_PLUGIN_NAME "SPUNAME"
59#define SPU_PTNOTE_SPUNAME ".note.spu_name"
60
61#endif /* _ELF_SPU_H */
